festival.introText:
Are you a fan of seeing some of the best dance, house and techno around? Then look no further than Newsam Park Festival. 

Anyone who was there knows Newsam Park's debut was next level. As soon as the last beat finished, thoughts turned to 2023. It promises to be even bigger and better.
 
After such a long time away from dancing, Newsam Park was one of the first festivals of the year and proved a huge release for everyone. The all-new Lake Stage provided special thrills in a gorgeous countryside setting, and a brand new sound system beefed up the beats to another level. Few captured the magic of dancing outdoors in the sunshine better than Folamour's colourful set, while Adam Beyer served up heavier techno funk later on in the day.
 
2023's event will build on that success.
 
See you down the front.

faqs.question: Travel Information
faqs.answer:
VENUE ADDRESS

Temple Newsam, Leeds, LS15 0AE

SHUTTLE BUSES

It is recommended buying your shuttle bus in advance, priority on the day will be for people who have purchased a ticket online.

It is advisable for all customers to buy online in advance to take advantage of the cheaper fares and to guarantee your seat.

Customers with online tickets will have first access to the priority bus queue on the day of the event.

ADDRESS:

Sovereign St, Leeds, LS1 4DA (outside KPMG office building)

INBOUND:

£9

Buses will run from 10.00 am

The last bus is 4pm *only for customers with shuttle bus tickets

OUTBOUND:

£9

The first bus departs from 9pm

The last bus departs 12:30am

faqs.question: Does Newsam Park have onsite camping?
faqs.answer: No, there are no onsite camping options available.

faqs.question: Are pre-payment plan tickets available?
faqs.answer: There are no pre-payment plans available at Newsam Park.

faqs.question: Does Newsam Park have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: The festival is strictly 18+ and a challenge 25 policy will be in operation at Newsam Park just like any pub, club or festival.

faqs.question: Can I bring my own food and drink into Newsam Park?
faqs.answer: Food and drink may not be brought on-site, there will be several food and drink stalls that will offer a great variety of healthy food considering local suppliers.

faqs.question: What if I cannot attend the festival?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.
